# CNAME File Instructions
# 
# This file is used to set up a custom domain for GitHub Pages
# 
# TO USE:
# 1. Rename this file from "CNAME.example" to "CNAME" (no extension)
# 2. Replace the text below with your actual domain name
# 3. Delete these comment lines (lines starting with #)
# 4. Commit and push to GitHub
# 
# EXAMPLE:
# www.stapleagency.com
# OR
# stapleagency.com
#
# Only include ONE domain name, nothing else

www.yourdomain.com
